* '''0.8.2''' — Tightened the resource-accounting stance: no-new-budget is now framed as a proposed rule contingent on native validation-cost review, with required invalid-signature, tail-latency, Bitcoin Core integration, implementation-variance, and individual/batch Schnorr baselines before activation. Clarified that the soft fork is additive at the output-type level but restrictive for the assigned QRS future leaf version after activation.
* '''0.8.1''' — Consistency fix: aligned the BIP's benchmark caveat with the benchmark harness, so both artifacts describe wrapper overhead as likely lowering the measured SLH-DSA/Schnorr ratio.
* '''0.8.0''' — Abstract scope tightened from destination framing to spend-path framing.
* '''0.7.0''' — Hardened the benchmark and its citation after review of the harness. Switched the headline figures from minimum to median timing; qualified the result as a Python-wrapper benchmark and noted that wrapper overhead likely lowers the measured SLH-DSA/Schnorr ratio; relabelled the SPHINCS+ implementation a preliminary proxy; and weakened the conclusion to "plausible and worth testing, not established," with the reference-implementation benchmark now required to report median and tail latency against a named library commit. The accompanying harness was updated to match.
* '''0.6.0''' — Final pre-posting edits (pre-review release). Labelled the benchmark non-consensus; softened the SPHINCS+ proxy from "faithful" to "preliminary"; and clarified that the BIP-342 sigops figure is a comparative cost model only, since QRS validation is a leaf-version rule and not a tapscript signature opcode that consumes the BIP-342 budget.
* '''0.5.0''' — Pre-posting polish. Softened backward-compatibility wording to defer to BIP-360's unrecognized-future-leaf-version rules rather than restate their semantics; made the resource-accounting framing dryer ("may already provide an adequate bound" rather than "over-prices"); replaced the "canonical/non-canonical encoding" requirement — undefined for fixed-length SLH-DSA artifacts — with a plain fixed-length acceptance rule, and added a Security Considerations note explaining why no encoding-canonicalization or low-S-style malleability rule is needed for this scheme.
* '''0.4.0''' — Added a preliminary verification benchmark to Resource Accounting. On one machine, SLH-DSA-SHA2-128s verification measured ≈ 22× a libsecp256k1 Schnorr verification. Reframed the binding threshold from the BIP-342 sigop-budget heuristic (≈ 157×) to the stricter per-block weight ratio (≈ 35×). The no-new-budget position remained provisional pending a FIPS 205 verifier on named production hardware.
* '''0.3.0''' — Second review pass. Resolved a witness-semantics contradiction (<code>qrs_signature</code> occupies the initial-stack position; this leaf version does have one initial stack element, not zero); corrected control-byte terminology (P2MR forces the low bit of <code>c[0]</code> high as an error-detection measure, not as a Taproot Y-parity bit); and pinned the SLH-DSA verification API to pure mode with an empty context string and canonical FIPS 205 encodings, removing a consensus-determinism ambiguity.
* '''0.2.0''' — Incorporated external review. Corrected the two-leaf sibling-leaf security language (in an OR tree the coin is spendable if the classical sibling is compromised, regardless of QRS-leaf safety); marked the leaf version provisional pending conflict review; made the no-new-budget resource-accounting position explicitly provisional pending benchmark, with a named comparison to libsecp256k1; clarified that <code>qrs_public_key</code> occupies the BIP-360 second-to-last witness-element position as a non-tapscript payload; clarified <code>ext_flag = 2</code> semantics; refined the spend-path framing; aligned the BIP header with the repository convention.
* '''0.1.0''' — Initial consolidated draft: P2MR-only SLH-DSA-SHA2-128s leaf, exact witness encoding, concrete (provisional) resource-accounting rule, composable-opcode roadmap deferred to Future Work.
